Goerg Files Second Suit Against Middelhoff, FT Deutschland Says

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-02-21T06:27:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/goerg-files-second-suit-against-middelhoff-ft-deutschland-says.html
German insolvency administrator
Klaus Hubert Goerg filed a second suit for exaggerated business
expenses and too high bonuses against Thomas Middelhoff, the
former chief executive officer of bankrupt retailer  Arcandor AG ,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported today, citing an
unidentified Goerg spokesman.  Middelhoff charged Arcandor for some private flights and
flights for his previous employer, the newspaper said, citing
Goerg. Middelhoff and some other executives at Arcandor also
received and agreed on bonuses that were too high, according to
the FTD.  “There hasn’t been any violation of duty by my client
Thomas Middelhoff,” the managers lawyer Winfried Holtermueller
said in an e-mailed statement, sent by Middelhoff’s spokesman
Feb. 19.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
